answer is going to be no.

00:13:59.920 --> 00:14:02.350
Let's go to another
idiosyncratic

00:14:02.350 --> 00:14:03.940
tactical question.

00:14:03.940 --> 00:14:06.810
When should you begin a new
diet or exercise program?

00:14:06.810 --> 00:14:09.050
Does it matter the
day that you begin?

00:14:09.050 --> 00:14:10.524
Of course it does.

00:14:10.524 --> 00:14:11.440
Let's talk about this.

00:14:11.440 --> 00:14:13.810
We're going to move
beyond the unit of a day.

00:14:13.810 --> 00:14:16.060
We're going to talk about
timing in a broader sense.

00:14:16.060 --> 00:14:17.643
There's some very
interesting research

00:14:17.643 --> 00:14:20.590
on what are called
"temporal landmarks."

00:14:20.590 --> 00:14:22.630
So think about a landmark
in physical space.

00:14:22.630 --> 00:14:25.090
What does a landmark
in physical space do?

00:14:25.090 --> 00:14:27.130
Get you to slow down
and pay attention.

00:14:27.130 --> 00:14:28.960
Helps you navigate, right?

00:14:28.960 --> 00:14:30.850
So there are also
temporal landmarks.

00:14:30.850 --> 00:14:32.440
There's some good research--

00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:33.760
a lot of research on this.

00:14:33.760 --> 00:14:36.135
Some of the best research is
done by researchers at Penn,

00:14:36.135 --> 00:14:39.110
including Katy Milkman, Jason
Reese, and Hengchen Dai,

00:14:39.110 --> 00:14:42.906
who's no longer at
Penn-- now at UCLA.

00:14:42.906 --> 00:14:44.030
Here's what they found out.

00:14:44.030 --> 00:14:46.930
There's certain dates
that seem to be better--

00:14:46.930 --> 00:14:51.664
make it more likely that people
will embark on behavior change.

00:14:51.664 --> 00:14:53.830
So you know this with New
Year's resolutions, right?

00:14:53.830 --> 00:14:56.520
Anybody ever made New
Year's resolutions?

00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:58.600
New Year's resolutions
get a lot of bad press.

00:14:58.600 --> 00:14:58.960
Here's the thing.

00:14:58.960 --> 00:15:00.460
New Year's resolutions--
oh, my God.

00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:03.850
Half the people don't even--

00:15:03.850 --> 00:15:06.580
half of New Year's
resolutions fail.

00:15:06.580 --> 00:15:10.960
To me, you've buried
the lead in that.

00:15:10.960 --> 00:15:13.810
I think the lead is that means
half of New Year's resolutions

00:15:13.810 --> 00:15:14.837
succeed.

00:15:14.837 --> 00:15:17.170
That's a big deal when you
think about how hard changing

00:15:17.170 --> 00:15:18.370
behavior is.

00:15:18.370 --> 00:15:19.130
That's a big deal.

00:15:19.130 --> 00:15:19.630
Why?

00:15:19.630 --> 00:15:21.500
Because all dates are
not created equal.

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:24.100
Some of them operate
as temporal landmarks,

00:15:24.100 --> 00:15:27.430
operating somewhat similar to
physical landmarks in space.

00:15:27.430 --> 00:15:29.200
What do these
temporal landmarks do?

00:15:29.200 --> 00:15:32.680
They trigger a peculiar
form of mental accounting.

00:15:32.680 --> 00:15:35.224
We open up a fresh ledger
on ourselves essentially,

00:15:35.224 --> 00:15:37.390
the same way a business
would open up a fresh ledger

00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:39.160
on a new quarter or a new year.

00:15:39.160 --> 00:15:41.080
So when they look
at the research

00:15:41.080 --> 00:15:44.650
on when people begin
behavior change-- and again,

00:15:44.650 --> 00:15:45.880
it's axiomatic.

00:15:45.880 --> 00:15:48.940
You're more likely to change
your behavior if you begin

00:15:48.940 --> 00:15:50.830
to try to change your behavior.

00:15:50.830 --> 00:15:54.370
You don't begin, your behavior
is not going to change, right?

00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:55.750
So what do we see?

00:15:55.750 --> 00:15:58.360
This is a study of a
very large university,

00:15:58.360 --> 00:16:00.996
and they were able to get
the data by looking at--

00:16:00.996 --> 00:16:02.870
when you go to the gym,
you have to swipe in.

00:16:02.870 --> 00:16:05.180
And so they had massive
amounts of data.

00:16:05.180 --> 00:16:06.450
When do people go to the gym?

00:16:06.450 --> 00:16:08.350
Start of a new
semester-- huge increase.

00:16:08.350 --> 00:16:09.400
Start of a new year--

00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:10.000
big increase.

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:11.180
Start of a new month--

00:16:11.180 --> 00:16:11.990
big increase.

00:16:11.990 --> 00:16:13.300
Start of a new week--

00:16:13.300 --> 00:16:14.470
very big increase.

00:16:14.470 --> 00:16:16.480
After your birthday-- a
somewhat big increase.

00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:19.030
This is mitigated by the fact
that there are decreases.

00:16:19.030 --> 00:16:21.700
There's a big drop in
going to the gym on the day

00:16:21.700 --> 00:16:24.280
after your 21st birthday.

00:16:24.280 --> 00:16:26.710
I'm not joking.

00:16:26.710 --> 00:16:28.519
So what do we know about that?

00:16:28.519 --> 00:16:29.560
What's our question here?

00:16:29.560 --> 00:16:31.330
Our question here is, when
should you begin a new diet

00:16:31.330 --> 00:16:33.280
or exercise program--
any behavior change?

00:16:33.280 --> 00:16:34.900
The day you choose to begin--

00:16:34.900 --> 00:16:36.830
those days are not
all created equal.

00:16:36.830 --> 00:16:38.960
You have a better chance if you
begin on a Monday rather than

00:16:38.960 --> 00:16:41.043
a Thursday, if you begin
on the first of the month

00:16:41.043 --> 00:16:43.220
rather than on the
13th of the month.

00:16:43.220 --> 00:16:45.497
You can choose personal
temporal landmarks.

00:16:45.497 --> 00:16:47.830
You're better off beginning
the day after your birthday,

00:16:47.830 --> 00:16:50.140
the day after your
anniversary working here

00:16:50.140 --> 00:16:52.720
than three days before that.

00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:54.580
Temporal landmarks
shape our behavior,

00:16:54.580 --> 00:16:56.230
help us change our behavior.

